<br>
MISSION:<br>
<br>
It is the goal of the Saryrn Guild Alliance to allow it's members the ability to keep the individuality that makes each guild unique. This union will enable it's members to embark on journies that they would otherwise not be able to complete alone. By retaining membership in SGA, smaller guilds can continue to remain a size that accommodates the guild, without sacrificing the opportunities that a larger guild would offer. Above all SGA is designed to ADD and aspect of fun and excitement to the game while keeping the close friendships that make this game special intact.<br>
<br>
<br>
THE SGA COUNCIL:<br>
<br>
The purpose of the SGA Council is to ensure that the interests of each guild are being represented fairly. Matters that will be decided by the council will include: The order or priority of proposed raids/events, decide disputes between SGA members which occurred during SGA events, accept or deny the application of a new member to the Alliance. If necessary the council has the responsiblity to be the catalyst for SGA events.<br>
<br>
1) Each guild will provide 1 diplomat who is the primary decision-makers for their guild. They will act as the contact to discuss interguild relations involving the Alliance.<br>
<br>
2) These diplomats will be chosen by the representative's respective guild in any manner that guild sees fit and will remain the diplomat for as long as that guild determines appropriate.<br>
<br>
3) The diplomats must be a member of the guild they were elected to represent, should the diplomat guildremove for any reason, they are immediately releaved of their duties on the SGA council<br>
<br>
4) The diplomats of each guild are required to vote for their respective guild. <br>
<br>
5) Each vote counts equal regardless of guild size.<br>
<br>
6) All votes that result in a tie will favor the status quo. It will take a majority vote to change the way SGA works.<br>
<br>
RAIDS/EVENTS:<br>
<br>
It is the intention of SGA to establish and mantain a reputation of hosting quality, efficient and fun events for all members involved. <br>
<br>
LOOT:<br>
<br>
Loot will always be &quot;Need before Greed&quot;. Certain raids will be designed to specifically retreive an item for one individual. All loot guidelines shall be posted on the Event board prior to the raid. Any loot that is not needed will be rolled on for by one representative from all attending guilds, the winner will add that item to their guild coffers and do as they see fit.<br>
<br>
<br>
COMMUNICATION:<br>
<br>
1) Event planning: Any member of the any SGA guild can propose to lead a raid. To do so they will submit the raid on the SGA message board in the Raid/event planning section<br>
<br>
2) Email of the Diplomats of each guild and the Raid/Event council members will be made available on the SGA site. These members may be contacted via this email address for issues that concern their respective duties in SGA.<br>
<br>
-------<br>
<br>
<br>
This is the SGA Charter, I hope it fits our needs well and will allow the SGA to grow and be very productive for the guilds involved.<br>
<br>
